  "pride_metadata": {
    "project": {
      "accession": "PXD020956",
      "title": "Porcine dermal extracellular matrix LC-MSMS",
      "additionalAttributes": [],
      "projectDescription": "Hitherto, microenvironments provided by dermal analogues could not avoid frequent split-thickness skin grafts (STSGs) failure and scar fibrosis. We reported a novel method assembling 3D-printed dermal analogues (PDAs) with porcine dermal extracellular matrix(dECM)'s recapitulated the latter\u2019s compositional and topological features. These optimized PADs reduced skin wounds contraction and improved cosmetic upshots proving superior to STSGs and commercially available dermal templates. Once grafted onto wounds beds, optimized PDAs evoked a type-2-like immune response, activated type-2 macrophages (M2-M\u03c6), upregulated anti-inflammatory genes like Wnt11, Fgf16 and ATF3, downregulated profibrotic genes like Il13r\u237a2, Itg\u237a11, and IL1\u03b2, and hindered fibrosis. Thus, PDAs' beneficial effects resulted from preserved dermis-specific ECM cues (by mass spectrometry analysis we identified more than 200 unique protein species inside our dECM powder) and well-balanced physicochemical properties, which collaboratively modulated crucial endogenous signaling pathways.",
      "sampleProcessingProtocol": "A protein assay based on Bradford's method (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA) using bovine serum albumin as the standard, determined the total protein content in acid-dissolved dECMp samples. To digest proteins, 0.05 M Tris (2-carboxyethyl) phosphine hydrochloride solution (TCEP, Sigma-Aldrich, USA; kept at 60\u00b0C for 60 min), 55 mM S-methyl-methanethiosulfonate (MMTS, Sigma-Aldrich, USA) in the dark at room temperature for 45 min), 100 \u03bcl of 8 M uric acid (pH = 8.5, Sigma-Aldrich, USA), and 100 \u03bcl of 0.25 M triethylammonium bicarbonate buffer (TEAB, Sigma-Aldrich, USA) were sequentially added to a solution 50 \u03bcg dECMp and spun down several times. After collection, the supernatant was proteolyzed to peptides first using 2% trypsin (Promega, USA) in 50 \u03bcl of 0.5M TEAB for 12 h at 37\u00b0C, then adding 1% trypsin for additional 4 h at 37\u00b0C. Adding 10 \u03bcl of 10% formic acid stopped the proteolytic activity. Peptide digests were analyzed via Liquid Chromatography/Mass Spectrometry (LC/MS), using a Thermo Scientific Q Exactive system (Thermo Fisher Scientific, USA).",
      "dataProcessingProtocol": "Protein identification was performed using the Mascot software (http://www.matrixscience.com). Database searches were carried out using the Uniprot Sus Scrofa database (http://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/9823). The Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes (KEGG) Orthology-based Annotation System 2.0 (KOBAS 2.0) was used to perform Gene Ontology (GO) and KEGG enrichment analyses.",
